Steps to run in VS Code
1.Open VS Code and create a file named image_resizer.py.

2.Paste the above code into the file.

3.Create a virtual environment (optional but recommended):
python -m venv venv
source venv/bin/activate   # macOS/Linux
venv\Scripts\activate      # Windows

4.Install Pillow:
pip install pillow

5.Press Ctrl + Shift + P → "Python: Select Interpreter" → choose your environment.

6.Run the script in VS Code terminal:
python image_resizer.py

7.Enter:
Path to your input folder (e.g., C:\Users\YourName\Pictures\input_images)
Path to your output folder (e.g., C:\Users\YourName\Pictures\output_images)
Width and height in pixels (e.g., 800 600)
